Under the expert guidance of the Founder at Oasis Arts Academy - Sambedana, students of Salaam Bombay Foundation's Academy of the Arts had the unique opportunity to attend a specially curated workshop. Here they learnt the nuances of art - how to create the perfect brush strokes, how to formulate perfectly blended backgrounds - unmissable facets that can help make or break an artist's vision.
 
Thank you, Sambedana, for making this tremendously insightful workshop possible!

@oasisartncrafts 
 
#SalaamBombayFoundation #AChildInSchoolHasAFuture #NGOIndia #ChangeMakers #HolisticLearning #Art #ArtsAcademy #Learning #Artists #Adolescents #Education

In a world fraught with unequal opportunities, acquiring skills can help one stand out from the crowd. And 21-year-old Karishma is a testament to this fact. 

Finding herself directionless and unsure of her next move after completing her graduation, she considers herself fortunate to enroll in the interview preparation programme under Salaam Bombay Foundation’s DreamLab initiative. 
Here she picked up and polished her communication, grooming, and etiquette skills, so when Trent Limited‘s Westside came calling, there was simply no turning back.

Today, she is a sales associate at the Westside store in Mumbai’s Army Navy building and is working hard to build a successful career. 
Her infectious smile and amicable personality have made her a favourite among customers and colleagues. She is grateful for this incredible workplace and thankful to her super supportive mentors and colleagues. 
We are super PROUD of her!
 
Working with a mega brand like Trent Limited‘s Westside is a distant dream for the many resource-challenged adolescents from Mumbai’s urban slums. 
To the girl child, the hurdles are even more pressing when despite completing their education, they are pushed into marriage when they cannot find suitable jobs. 
In losing their power to sustain themselves, they also lose the confidence to stand up for themselves. 
We are grateful for the support received from Trent Limited, who continues to empower our students and, most importantly, provides them with opportunities that resound with their constant belief in us!

@westsidestores @arshiyamecklai 

#SalaamBombay #AChildInSchoolHasAFuture #NGOIndia #ChangeMakers #GiveBack #LiteracyMatters #HolisticLearning #ConversationalEnglish #LearningEnglish #SpeakingEnglish #Communication #Skills

Each time we walk into our vocational training centres, our hearts are full of joy. 
It is surprisingly silent - the commotion of a classroom replaced with the tinkering of tools, rapt attention to the blackboard displaced with students engrossed in learning skills such as Mobile Repair, Makeup, Hair styling, etc.

We get to experience the saying - that if given a chance to be involved, children will learn.
 
With Trent Limited‘s support, the skills@school program at Salaam Bombay Foundation has empowered over 400 students in Mumbai and Pune. 

@WestsideStores @arshiyamecklai

Hailing from the slums of Mumbai, Shailesh is a 20-year-old photography enthusiast, who always dreamed of making it big in the world of photography and film-making.

Shailesh saw an opportunity to pursue his passion when he joined Salaam Bombay Foundation’s Media Academy. His dedication and hard work finally paid off when he bagged a fully paid scholarship worth 25 lakhs from @whistling_woods. We are ever so grateful to Whistling Woods International for helping support the dreams of underprivileged students of our country.

@sk.picktures

Many of our students are receiving scholarships from eminent academies to further their education in areas of their interest and we are over the moon!
 
SBF wishes our young change-makers the very best as they continue their educational journeys and build brighter futures for themselves. 

NOTE: Please note that SBF is NOT providing any scholarships, at the moment. Our students are receiving these scholarships from eminent academies.

At-risk youth from urban slums are often unable to pursue higher education due to financial constraints. Through their training at Salaam Bombay Foundation, they are able to access internships, work experiences, and scholarships!

These scholarships help underprivileged adolescents build sustainable careers in their area of interest.

We are grateful to Mr. Anupam Kher and @actorprepares for recognizing the hidden talent in our students and offering three of them a two-month in-person training course and a chance to audition for some of the biggest production houses. Our students are super thrilled, and so are we! We can’t wait to see what the future holds for them.

#SalaamBombay #AChildInSchoolHasAFuture #NGOIndia #ChangeMakers #HolisticLearning #Learning #Adolescents #Education #Acting #Theatre #Scholarships

Salaam Bombay Foundation turned 20 this year!

Over the past two decades, we have impacted the lives of more than 5 lakh at-risk adolescents from urban slums of India.

Amongst the countless success stories of Salaam Bombay Foundation students aiming for the stars and going beyond, we must admit we have a special place in our hearts for our Alumni who have decided to join the Salaam Bombay Foundation family as trainers, facilitators, and project leads. It takes burning passion and oodles of courage to work with us as change agents at the grassroots level.

Hear our young stars share their milestones at Salaam Bombay Foundation and what keeps them going...

#SalaamBombay #AChildInSchoolHasAFuture #NGOIndia #ChangeMakers #HolisticLearning #Learning #Adolescents #Education #FoundationDay #Anniversary #TwentyYears

Over the past 20 years, Salaam Bombay Foundation has been at the forefront of educating young India on the ill effects of substance abuse, especially Tobacco.

In line with our mission, we work with at-risk youth from urban slums empowering them with life-changing knowledge on the importance of preventive behaviors, nutrition on a budget, fitness, and sound mental health.

We are thrilled that we could take our message to a much larger audience with the help of Tapu Sena on the popular television series, ‘Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah.’

A sneak-peek into the special workshop conducted by @actorprepares for our students.

The institute founded by international actor Anupam Kher, will also offer scholarships to select exceptionally talented students from municipal run schools in an attempt to help these resource challenged acting aspirants build a career as actors and performers. 

The workshop was organised with a motive to teach at-risk adolescents from urban slums the finer aspects of the performing art, improve their skills and guide them on their path to pursue acting professionally.

@imchetan.official and 30 other actors from our Theatre Academy got once-in-a-lifetime opportunity to be part of a specially designed workshop by @actorprepares 
A day before the workshop, Chetan was on an emotional rollercoaster... nervous but excited, anxious and yet ready-to-prove himself...

Meet Antakshari Surendra Piwal, a 17-year-old student at Salaam Bombay Foundation's Theatre Academy. Determined and full of life, this young adolescent hailing from the slums of Mumbai is one tough cookie indeed!
Braving the odds in pursuit of her dream of becoming an actor, she is currently pulling night shifts at a local nursing home. 

When asked about her role in the play, Julius Ceasar, she beams, “I am part of the crowd. My role may be small today, but I have big dreams, and this is only the beginning!”.

To know more about our students' work, click the link in our bio!

What happens when school students take on the challenge to revitalise their community's health?

At the heart of Mumbai's bustling neighbourhoods, a quiet revolution is underway—a movement that challenges the norms of a sedentary lifestyle and redefines community health. Salaam Bombay Foundation's Sports Academy is at the forefront of this transformation, championing the cause of fitness and empowerment among resource-challenged adolescents.

How does this initiative, which appears deceptively simple, manage to break the cycle of inactivity that grips so many? The answer lies in the strategic deployment of "Fitizens," a title given to students who, through rigorous training, become Fitness Monitors in their communities. Armed with simple yet effective exercise routines that require minimal space and equipment, these young leaders are redefining public spaces. From parks to terraces, gullies to maidans, they conduct engaging fitness classes that resonate with a wide audience.

The numbers speak volumes. Since the programme's inception, over 200 Fitizens have trained more than 9,726 community members, making fitness accessible and inclusive. But the story doesn't end with statistics. It's a narrative of transformation, where each step taken in a fitness class echoes the broader mission of inspiring change and fostering a healthier future.

Join us as we delve deeper into the stories of these Fitizens and their remarkable journey of empowerment and transformation. Together, we are not just promoting fitness; we are reshaping lives, one community at a time. @fitindiaoff @dptofsportsgoi #SalaamBombayFoundation #FitnessForAll #TransformingLives

latestPosts.caption:
Meet Raj, an 8th grader from a government school in Mumbai, who turned a disturbing sight - tobacco litter and spitting, into a powerful movement for change.
While many walked past, Raj stood up. With the encouragement of his principal and the transformative support of Salaam Bombay Foundation’s Preventive Health Education Programme (PHEP), Raj not only gained critical awareness about the dangers of tobacco but also developed essential life skills like leadership, communication, and determination. These tools empowered him to pioneer the cause for a tobacco-free school, turning his concern into a powerful campaign for change.

•	He and his friends created awareness through drawings and campaigns.
•	He mobilised his peers and inspired even the school staff.
•	His school became tobacco-free and soon, so did the entire neighbourhood!

Even the school’s watchman, once part of the problem, became a protector of the cause.
Salaam Bombay Foundation is proud of students like Raj, who use life skills to uplift their communities and inspire a healthier, brighter future for all.

Share this story to inspire more young leaders or tag someone who believes in the power of adolescents.

If you ever needed proof that big dreams can grow from the smallest beginnings, you only need to look at @imchetan.official.

Starting at our Theatre Academy, Chetan did not just learn acting. He learnt resilience, collaboration, discipline and the quiet confidence that comes from knowing you have something important to say. What began as small performances on local stages soon grew into something much larger.

Today, Chetan stands tall among young artists who are shaping India’s creative future. From acting in The Disciple on Netflix, a film that travelled across global film circuits, to contributing to The Legend of Hanuman, Aatmapamphlet, and Manvat Murders, he has built a portfolio that speaks of talent, determination, and a refusal to settle for anything less than excellence.

Chetan’s journey reminds us that opportunity is often invisible to the eye. It begins backstage. It starts in small rooms where young minds are nurtured and encouraged to dream beyond their postcode. It is shaped by mentors, moments of doubt, and the courage to audition for something bigger than your present.

At Salaam Bombay Foundation, we believe every young person has this spark. Chetan Wagh is proof of what happens when that spark is protected, fed and fanned until it lights up the world.

This is not just a story of an artist finding his stage. It is a story of a young man reclaiming his future through the arts and inviting others to dream a little bigger too.

#SalaamBombayFoundation #Changemakers #TheatreAcademy #ArtsForChange #fromstagetoscreen

We’ve always loved stories. Telling them. Listening to them. Living them.

Rooted in the rich tradition of folk theatre, our latest Marathi play — Ahankarak Kahankarakachi Gosht, brought to life by the talented students of our Theatre Academy, draws inspiration from the vibrant world of the Warli community.

Blending music, movement, and storytelling, the play explores tradition, ego, and identity in a way that is both reflective and relatable. It’s a story that begins with ‘them’ and ends up being about ‘us’. This one’s for everyone who has ever lost themselves in a story.

Catch the performance live:
Saturday, 26 April | 11:00 AM | Yashwant Natya Mandir, Matunga, Mumbai
Entry Free

On Thursday, 17 April, we had the pleasure of hosting employees from Cornerstone OnDemand at Gauri Dutt School, Sion, where they joined us in distributing starter kits to our budding entrepreneurs.

These kits are more than just tools. They’re a launchpad for self-belief, skill-building, and earning potential. From mobile repair to beauty, bakery, and more, each kit is tailored to the student's chosen trade, empowering them to start their journey towards entrepreneurship and financial independence.

A heartfelt thank you to Cornerstone OnDemand for standing by our mission and for being there in person to witness how far a little support can go in helping young people break the cycle of limitation and unlock a future of possibilities.

What happens when young entrepreneurs are given the mic, the stage, and the belief that their ideas matter? You get Dolphin Tanki 4.0. Thirty-six gritty, bold, brilliant minds pitched not for applause, but for action. For the first time, rural changemakers joined the city’s sharpest, proving that innovation doesn’t need a fancy address. Seed funding was won, mindsets were shifted, and futures were reimagined. This was more than a competition. It was a launchpad. 

A heartfelt thanks to our partners SVKM's Narsee Monjee Institute of Management Studies @nmims_india (NMIMS) Mumbai, Narotam Sekhsaria Family Office, and @YuWaahIndia at UNICEF for their unwavering support in empowering these talented minds.

Here’s a glimpse into the excitement, determination, and innovation that unfolded at Dolphin Tanki 4.0! From game-changing pitches to inspiring stories of perseverance, the event brought together young entrepreneurs from urban and rural India, ready to rewrite their futures.

These moments captured the spirit of Dolphin Tanki as dreams meet opportunities, as ambition turns into action, where the next generation of business leaders is nurtured.

Dolphin Tanki 4.0 is here—bigger, bolder, and making an impact like never before! This entrepreneurial platform, powered by the NMIMS School of Business Management and Salaam Bombay Foundation, provides grants, mentorship, and real business opportunities to young grassroots entrepreneurs.

With a ₹1 million funding pool, rural expansion, and participants from Mumbai, Pune, Nashik, and Kolkata, we’re transforming vocational skills into thriving businesses. Stay tuned as these young changemakers redefine their futures!

#DolphinTanki #NMIMS #EmpoweringEntrepreneurs #SocialImpact

latestPosts.caption:
After weeks of preparation, mentorship, and determination, the moment has arrived. The finalists of Dolphin Tanki 4.0 will pitch their ventures to an exceptional panel of industry leaders, each bringing a wealth of expertise across beauty, technology, consumer electronics, and hospitality.

Meet the jury who will be evaluating the next generation of young entrepreneurs:

Pravesh Saha – General Manager, South Asia, Wella

Aby John– Co-Founder and Chief Operating Officer, 88 Pictures

Rajavi Shah – Head of Marketing, Kiro Beauty

Manohar Nadigatla – Group Key Account Manager (DGM), Modern Retail, LG Electronics

Pankaj Pandey – Chief Operating Officer, Onsitego

Zulekha Badar – Pastry Chef

These industry stalwarts will not just assess business potential but will also mentor and guide young entrepreneurs as they take their ventures to the next level.

Who will secure the funding? Who will impress the jury? The finals are here.
